This privacy policy governs the manner in which Light in a Box collects, uses, maintains and discloses information collected from users (each, a "User") of the Light in a Box application.

Personal identification information

To the best of my knowledge, I have not programmed this app to collect any personally identifiable information. All data (app preferences (Volume setting, difficulty, etc.) created by the you (the user) is stored on your device only, and can be simply erased by clearing the app's data or uninstalling it.
Privacy Policy for Light in a Box

Advertising

Our App runs Unity Ads, a third-party advertising service, which may collect non-personal identification information about users in order to display ads that are relevant to them. We do not share any personal identification information with Unity Ads.

Sharing your personal information

We do not collect or share any personal identification information with third parties.

Changes to this privacy policy

We have the discretion to update this privacy policy at any time. When we do, we will post a notification on the main page of our App. We encourage Users to frequently check this page for any changes to stay informed about how we are helping to protect the personal information we collect. You acknowledge and agree that it is your responsibility to review this privacy policy periodically and become aware of modifications.

Your acceptance of these terms

By using this App, you signify your acceptance of this policy. If you do not agree to this policy, please do not use our App. Your continued use of the App following the posting of changes to this policy will be deemed your acceptance of those changes.

Contacting us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, the practices of this App, or your dealings with this App, please post a discussion on GitHub.

This privacy policy was last updated on 14/2/23.
